This article contains major spoilers for the final of RuPaul’s Drag Race UK vs. The World. RuPaul’s Drag Race UK vs. The World crowned its winner on Tuesday night in a finale that truly got everyone talking. After a season that gave us a meat-throwing talent show, some seriously shady moments (including from the guest judges!) and more shock eliminations than any series before it, RuPaul crowned Blu Hydrangea  the inaugural “Queen Of The Mothertuckin’ World” ahead of Baga Chipz, Jujubee and runner-up Mo Heart. Here’s just a selection of what fans had to say over the course of the episode... The entire season of RuPaul’s Drag Race UK vs. The World is now available to stream on BBC iPlayer.